COPYING.provenance — per-file porting provenance for @session.js/calls
========================================================================

License decision (plan D10): everything shipped in this package is licensed
AGPL-3.0-or-later. Official Session clients are GPLv3 (session-android,
session-ios) and AGPLv3 (session-desktop). GPLv3 code combines into an
AGPLv3 work per AGPLv3 §13. All upstream copyright notices are preserved in
the headers of ported files, and changes are annotated ("modified"), as GPL
requires. © of ported portions: Session Foundation.

PORTED FILES
------------

src/fsm/state-machine.ts
  Ported from session-android
  `app/src/main/java/org/thoughtcrime/securesms/webrtc/data/StateMachine.kt`
  (GPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified (Kotlin → TypeScript table-driven
  port; two documented supplementary rows added for the caller-side
  local-pre-offer ambiguity — see the in-file comment and
  docs/evidence/P2-T1.md). Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/supervisor.ts
  Gating/dispatch logic ported from session-android
  `org/session/libsession/messaging/calls/CallMessageProcessor.kt` (GPLv3)
  and session-desktop `ts/receiver/callMessage.ts` (AGPLv3), © Session
  Foundation, modified (adapted to structural SessionLike/SignalingSender/
  MediaEngine interfaces; single-device headless operation).
  The mid-call ICE reconnect behavior (P6-T1: initiator restart loop,
  non-initiator ≤60 s wait, exhaustion handling) is ported from
  session-android `webrtc/WebRtcCallBridge.kt` /
  `webrtc/PeerConnectionWrapper.kt` (GPLv3), © Session Foundation,
  modified. Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/call.ts
  The public Call handle's sequencing and edge-case behavior (inbound-only
  action guards, consumer-callback containment) adapted from session-desktop
  `ts/session/utils/calling/CallManager.ts` (AGPLv3), © Session Foundation,
  modified (structural dependency interfaces; werift media plane; headless
  operation). Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/call-manager.ts
  Call lifecycle wiring adapted from session-desktop
  `ts/session/utils/calling/CallManager.ts` (AGPLv3) and the ICE-restart
  wiring from session-android `webrtc/WebRtcCallBridge.kt` /
  `webrtc/PeerConnectionWrapper.kt` (GPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified
  (SessionLike/CallSupervisor composition; werift media plane; trickle-ICE
  arming; diagnostics + error containment). Licensed under
  AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/media/peer-connection.ts
  Peer-connection configuration (max-bundle, rtcp-mux, Opus preference,
  Android-parity SDP munging, negotiated "signaling" data channel id 548)
  ported from session-android `webrtc/PeerConnectionWrapper.kt` (GPLv3) and
  session-desktop `ts/session/utils/calling/CallManager.ts` (AGPLv3),
  © Session Foundation, modified (werift glue, ICE-state mapping and
  teardown written fresh). Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

src/media/audio-bridge.ts, src/media/codec.ts, src/media/sdp.ts,
src/media/dsp.ts
  PCM↔Opus bridge and SDP munging per plan §4.7; munging rules ported from
  session-android `PeerConnectionWrapper.kt` (GPLv3) / session-desktop
  (AGPLv3), © Session Foundation, modified; werift glue, codec abstraction
  and DSP helpers written fresh. Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

FRESH-WRITTEN FILES
-------------------

src/types.ts        — written fresh (normative §4.3 API surface). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/errors.ts       — written fresh (P6-T3 error taxonomy). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/policy.ts       — written fresh (freshness windows from §3.1/§3.2 facts;
                      TURN constants are the public values shipped in every
                      official Session client, Appendix B). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/signaling.ts    — written fresh (SessionSignaling over SessionLike;
                      TrickleIceSender batching per §3.2/§4.6; enum/literal
                      type-bridge documentation). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
src/index.ts        — written fresh (barrel). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
test/**             — written fresh. SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
examples/**         — written fresh (voice-agent + offline-echo demos,
                      pluggable STT/TTS interfaces). SPDX: AGPL-3.0-or-later.

NORMATIVE-TABLE RESTORATION
---------------------------

src/fsm/state-machine.ts
  Ported from session-android StateMachine.kt (GPLv3) as before; the P6-T1
  work restored the normative Appendix C `network-reconnect` event (the
  non-initiator's entry into `reconnecting`) that the P2 port had omitted —
  plan data, not upstream code. © of the original port: Session Foundation.
  Licensed under AGPL-3.0-or-later.

